      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:14:4",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) عَنِ الْفَأْرَةِ وَ الْكَلْبِ يَقَعُ فِي السَّمْنِ وَ الزَّيْتِ ثُمَّ يَخْرُجُ مِنْهُ حَيّاً فَقَالَ لَا بَأْسَ بِأَكْلِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Ali Bin Al Noman, from Saeed Al A’araj who said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about the mouse and the dog which fall into the butter and the oil, then come out alive from it’. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no problem with eating it’."
        ]
      }
    },
